Package presentation.epiphyte

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    I_Inspector
    inspectors are in charge of gathering and providing indicators value
    each inspector may be specific of a component of the simulation (population, genetics, ...)
    inspectors are unknown of the thing objects (epiphyte system approach)
    within a given protocol, all inspectors are managed by the protocol class
    most inspectors are bound to the A_Inspector abstract class which gather generic inspector function
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    A_Inspector
    Data inspector: retrieves informations e.g. population sizes and manages lists. stores the values of the indicators to be recorded in the general indicators file.
    C_InspectorBorreliaCrocidurae
    Data inspector: retrieves informations about ticks.
    C_InspectorCMR
    manage traps and tagged rodents list, computes the global indicators from the retrieved individual values indicator definitions
    C_InspectorFossorialRodents
    Data inspector: retrieves information on burrow systems and manages lists.
    C_InspectorGenetic
    Retrieves information on genes and alleles of the whole population.
    C_InspectorHybrid
    From case study number 2 - MBour M2 A.Comte
    C_InspectorOrnithodorosSonrai
    Data inspector: retrieves informations about ticks.
    C_InspectorPopulation
    Data inspector: retrieves informations e.g. population sizes and manages lists.
    C_InspectorTransportation
    From case study number 3 - Senegal Centenal M2 P.A.Mboup
    C_InspectorVegetation
    Data inspector: retrieves informations e.g. la liste des végétations.
